The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A 65-year-old man committed suicide by jumping in front of a Dum Dum-bound Metro Railway train at Sovabazar-Sutanuti station on Monday morning. Police said Niranjan Majumder, a resident of Jorabagan, was suffering from depression. Trains were disrupted for 50 minutes.    Kakoli Mondal, 24, a homemaker at Mahisbathan in Tarulia, under New Town police station, was killed when a pipe gun that her husband Ramesh, 29, a construction material supplier, had brought home on Monday afternoon accidentally went off. Kakoli died at RG Kar Hospital. Ramesh is absconding.    Two helpers died and the driver of a truck was critically injured after the vehicle hit a stationary truck in Uluberia on NH6 on Monday morning.    Suraj Kumar Yadav, 20, was run over by a truck on BT Road, at Baranagar, on Sunday night after falling off his motorcycle.    The 315/316 Howrah-Adra-Chakradharpur passenger, 315A/ 316A Howrah-Adra-Bokaro passenger and the 353/354 Kharagpur-Tata passenger have been cancelled till June 2.        old his wife that a friend had asked him to keep the gun for a few days but she wanted him to get rid of it. In the scuffle that followed, the gun accidentally went off and the bullet hit her on the chest. She was taken to RG Kar Hospital, where she died in the evening. Ramesh is absconding.                                                                                                                                               
